  "prompt": "Why did Christ die?",
  "response": "Christian theology teaches that Jesus Christ died for the sins of humanity. According to the New Testament, especially the Gospels and various epistles, His death is viewed as a sacrificial act to atone for the sins of mankind, offering redemption and reconciliation with God. This concept is central to Christian beliefs, particularly regarding salvation and the grace of God. Different Christian denominations might have varying interpretations, but the essential idea is that Christ\u2019s death is seen as a means of providing forgiveness and eternal life to believers.",
